'''Fernandino Cona''' (1882 <U+2013> unknown) was an Italian military officer who participated in [[World War II]]. 

His positions included Commanding Officer, 21st Brigade Granatieri di Sardegna, General Officer Commanding 7th Division Leonessa (1939), General Officer Commanding XV Corps (1940), General Officer Commanding XX Corps, North Africa (1940<U+2013>41).<ref>[http://www.generals.dk/general/Cona/Fernandino/Italy.html Short sketch of Cona] at Generals.dk, accessed 1 September 2009</ref>

He took over as commander-in-chief of Italian forces near [[Benghazi]] when General Tellera was killed in action at the [[Beda Fomm|battle of Beda Fomm]] in February 1941.<ref>[[Alan Moorehead]], ''Mediterranean Front'', 1941</ref> His command was short lived as he was captured by Allied forces during the same battle.

